import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['temp_range'] = data['temp_max'] - data['temp_min']
    avg_temp_range = data.groupby('year')['temp_range'].mean()
    
    plt.plot(avg_temp_range.index, avg_temp_range.values)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the average temperature range (temp_max - temp_min) per year?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    total_precipitation = data.groupby('location')['precipitation'].sum()
    total_precipitation.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of precipitation across different locations?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['wind'], data['temp_max'])
    plt.xlabel('Wind')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between wind and temperature?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    weather_counts = data['weather'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(weather_counts, labels=weather_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the most common weather condition across all locations?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['avg_temp'] = (data['temp_max'] + data['temp_min']) / 2
    
    yearly_avg_temp = data.groupby('year')['avg_temp'].mean()
    
    plt.plot(yearly_avg_temp.index, yearly_avg_temp.values)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of temperature over the years?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
